    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Platforms on which milk churns are places for collection by cart or truck, once a common roadside site found in the dairy farming areas of Britain. While some were simple contructions made of wood, the majority were built from stone or concrete blocks. </Note_Text>
